133
00:12:19,026 --> 00:12:26,130
[SPEAKER_00]: for people on mass health, things like eviction support, tenancy rent deposits, all of that.

134
00:12:26,931 --> 00:12:32,334
[SPEAKER_00]: And then what you're saying about, we're calling it justice involved.

135
00:12:33,255 --> 00:12:41,920
[SPEAKER_00]: The Medicaid program has historically never been used to cover folks that have been incarcerated.

136
00:12:41,940 --> 00:12:42,561
[SPEAKER_12]: Right.

137
00:12:43,601 --> 00:13:09,648
[SPEAKER_00]: Progressive states have asked the federal government to waive that, and now folks can receive up to two months of pre-release services, which are intended to help them get set up in the community, so that when they're released, they have a source of care, they have support, they have all of the resources to be successful.

138
